observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the person in-charge for the titling of parcels of land to:
• request/ask help from other government agencies on how to secure the titles for Items 1 to 3 of Annex J;
• expedite the application of Special Patent and submit all the documents needed for Items 4 to 13 of Annex J;
• support the claim that the Municipality does not own Item 14 of Annex J;
• provide a copy of the documents to the Municipal Accountant for Item 15 to 20 of Annex J as basis for dropping from the books of accounts; and
• expedite the processing of land title for Items 21 to 27 of Annex J.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the person in-charge for the titling of the parcels of land to:
• request/ask help from other government agencies on how to secure the titles for Items 1 to 3 of Annex I wherein no available documents can be found in the Municipality;
• secure the approval of the Sangguniang Bayan for the Municipality’s application of Special Patent and submit all the documents needed for Items 4 to 12 of Annex I; 
• support the claim that the Municipality does not own Item 13 of Annex I recorded in the books of accounts; 
• provide a copy of the documents to the Municipal Accountant for Item 14 and 15 of Annex I as basis for dropping from the books of accounts; and 
• expedite the processing of land title for Items 16 to 28 of Annex I; 
• provide a copy of the documents for the unrecorded land covered by Title No. T402631 as basis for recording by the Municipal Accountant; and
• require the Municipal Accountant to record the cost directly attributable to the acquisition of land as part of the purchase price and not as separate land items.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
• request the Sangguniang Bayan for a Resolution to authorize him to file the request for write-off of uncollectible receivables totaling P250,000.00;
• require the Municipal Accountant to set up the provision for Allowance for Impairment in order to present fairly the receivables account in the financial statements at net realizable amount consistent with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2016-005 and for the fair presentation of the accounts in the financial statements as required under Paragraph 27 of IPSAS 1.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
• allot adequate time to accomplish the renewal of PAR of PPE with over three years after issuance; 
• prepare the PAR and issue to end users for PPE acquired during the year totaling P3,195,786.00; 
• ensure that PAR is renewed every three years or whenever there is a change in custodianship, in compliance with the existing rules and regulations; and
• facilitate monitoring of PPE for inventory taking purposes and to establish full accountability.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the members of the Local School Board to:
prepare a balanced budget with conscious and concerted efforts of observing compliance with the legal and regulatory requirements on SEF budgeting, allocation and utilization;
refrain from accommodating expenditures for activities for which the DepEd has the direct mandate to execute;
request for input from the DepEd officials or Schools Division Superintendent on the prioritization of SEF projects and expenditures in accordance with the DepEd criteria and with due regard to the provisions of laws, rules and regulations prescribing the limitations on the use of the fund; and
maximize the utilization of SEF to attain its objectives, monitor the implementation of the projects/programs and activities (PPAs), and take appropriate actions such as realignment or reprogramming, if necessary.
